name: Arsenal
summary: Arsenal made a significant statement in the Premier League title race with a record-breaking victory over Chelsea, asserting their dominance at the top of the standings. In the North London derby, Arsenal emerged victorious against Tottenham Hotspur in a thrilling 3-2 encounter. Arsenal's triumph over their rivals was highlighted by an impressive performance from Martin Odegaard. Meanwhile, Kai Havertz's goal added to Chelsea's woes, while Mikel Arteta's team extended their lead atop the league table. The club's recent success has also garnered attention from unexpected quarters, with actress Anne Hathaway expressing her support for the Gunners. Additionally, Arsenal defender Kieran Tierney expressed his contentment upon returning to the team after a long absence. However, in the Women's Super League, Arsenal was held to a 1-1 draw by Everton, preventing them from securing an outright victory.

name: Al Maktoum International Airport
summary: The United Arab Emirates is investing heavily in expanding its aviation infrastructure. Dubai International Airport (DXB) is already one of the busiest in the world, and the new Al Maktoum International Airport (DWC) is set to become even larger. The $35 billion expansion plan for DWC includes the construction of a new passenger terminal, which will make it the world's largest airport by capacity. The new terminal will have 400 gates and will be able to handle up to 160 million passengers per year. The expansion is expected to be completed by 2025 and will make Dubai a major global aviation hub.
